        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Examine the value of the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.CheckBox.Checked%2A&gt;</ph> property to determine its state, and use that value to set an option.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the code sample below, when the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.CheckBox&gt;</ph> control's <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.CheckBox.CheckedChanged&gt;</ph> event is raised, the form's <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.AllowDrop%2A&gt;</ph> property is set to <ph id="ph4">`false`</ph> if the check box is checked.</source>
        </trans-unit>
